The report also raises the issue of the deep-rooted principle of personal autonomy, which is respected for sexuality. - Spokesperson of the Sant’Egidio Community   One of the fundamental considerations of our proposal is separating – deliberately - the "before" and the "after" the abortion . Because the real embryo and the real child are not part of any possible abortion, but the victim of one. So it could be denied to this - public - protection to this "proper person" (legal category of any human being) in consideration of ONE of its constituents (social, national, legal, family, etc.). The logic of "after" abortion is completely different. Indeed, equated with unintended non-intentional consequences, it is influenced in its autonomy by another factor, another actor. But this will be further developed below. To deal with the "vertical" or "horizontal" separation "in relation" is of course an open variable of this study. In the society of autonomy, that's the main question. Abortion = social abortion In a society of autonomy, where the individual autonomy dominates, one of the considerations is essentially social, and that has already given rise to an "immense confusion between the person and the citizen or the person as an individual and as a social being."
